#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.249"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.249:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.249:0.2"
msgid "25. Duccaritavagga "
msgstr "25. Bad Conduct "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: sivathikasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.249:0.3"
msgid "249. Sivathikasutta "
msgstr "249. A Charnel Ground "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: sivathikāya → sīvathikāya (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.249:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā sivathikāya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five drawbacks to a charnel ground. "

msgctxt "an5.249:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.249:1.3"
msgid "Asuci, duggandhā, sappaṭibhayā, vāḷānaṃ amanussānaṃ āvāso, bahuno janassa ārodanā—"
msgstr "It’s filthy, stinking, frightening, a gathering place for savage monsters, and a weeping place for many people. "

msgctxt "an5.249:1.4"
msgid "ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā sivathikāya. "
msgstr "These are the five drawbacks of a charnel ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.269, sc2
msgctxt "an5.249:2.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcime ādīnavā sivathikūpame puggale. "
msgstr "In the same way there are five drawbacks of a person like a charnel ground. "

msgctxt "an5.249:2.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.249:2.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo asucinā kāyakammena samannāgato hoti; "
msgstr "To start with, some person has filthy conduct by way of body, speech, and mind. "

msgctxt "an5.249:2.4"
msgid "asucinā vacīkammena samannāgato hoti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.249:2.5"
msgid "asucinā manokammena samannāgato hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an5.249:2.6"
msgid "Idamassa asucitāya vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is how they’re filthy, I say. "

msgctxt "an5.249:2.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā asuci; "
msgstr "That person is just as filthy as a charnel ground. "

msgctxt "an5.249:2.8"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.249:3.1"
msgid "Tassa asucinā kāyakammena samannāgatassa, asucinā vacīkammena samannāgatassa, asucinā manokammena samannāgatassa pāpako kittisaddo abbhuggacchati. "
msgstr "Because of their filthy conduct, they get a bad reputation. "

msgctxt "an5.249:3.2"
msgid "Idamassa duggandhatāya vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is how they’re stinky, I say. "

msgctxt "an5.249:3.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā duggandhā; "
msgstr "That person is just as stinky as a charnel ground. "

msgctxt "an5.249:3.4"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.249:4.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ asucinā kāyakammena samannāgataṃ, asucinā vacīkammena samannāgataṃ, asucinā manokammena samannāgataṃ pesalā sabrahmacārī ārakā parivajjanti. "
msgstr "Because of their filthy conduct, good-hearted spiritual companions avoid them from afar. "

msgctxt "an5.249:4.2"
msgid "Idamassa sappaṭibhayasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "That’s how they’re frightening, I say. "

msgctxt "an5.249:4.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā sappaṭibhayā; "
msgstr "That person is just as frightening as a charnel ground. "

msgctxt "an5.249:4.4"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.249:5.1"
msgid "So asucinā kāyakammena samannāgato, asucinā vacīkammena samannāgato, asucinā manokammena samannāgato sabhāgehi puggalehi saddhiṃ saṃvasati. "
msgstr "Because of their filthy conduct, they live together with people of a similar character. "

msgctxt "an5.249:5.2"
msgid "Idamassa vāḷāvāsasmiṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is how they gather with savage monsters, I say. "

msgctxt "an5.249:5.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā vāḷānaṃ amanussānaṃ āvāso; "
msgstr "That person is just as much a gathering place of savage monsters as a charnel ground. "

msgctxt "an5.249:5.4"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
#. VAR: khīyadhammaṃ → khīyanadhammaṃ (bj) | khiyadhammaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.249:6.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ asucinā kāyakammena samannāgataṃ, asucinā vacīkammena samannāgataṃ, asucinā manokammena samannāgataṃ pesalā sabrahmacārī disvā khīyadhammaṃ āpajjanti: "
msgstr "Because of their filthy conduct, when good-hearted spiritual companions see them they complain: "

msgctxt "an5.249:6.2"
msgid "‘aho vata no dukkhaṃ ye mayaṃ evarūpehi puggalehi saddhiṃ saṃvasāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Oh, it’s so painful for us to have to live together with such as these.’ "

msgctxt "an5.249:6.3"
msgid "Idamassa ārodanāya vadāmi. "
msgstr "This is how there’s weeping, I say. "

msgctxt "an5.249:6.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi sā, bhikkhave, sivathikā bahuno janassa ārodanā; "
msgstr "This person is just as much a weeping place for many people as a charnel ground. "

msgctxt "an5.249:6.5"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.249:6.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca ādīnavā sivathikūpame puggale”ti. "
msgstr "These are the five drawbacks of a person like a charnel ground.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.249:6.7"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

